Diagnosis. MALE. The mandible is broadly dilated with a bilobate dorsal lamella (
Fig. 48
); the axilla is posterolaterally produced and truncate posteriorly; the first metasomal segment is subsessile with the second (
Fig. 41
); the free length of the paramere is slightly dorsoventrally flattened and initially downcurved toward the apex, but the extreme apex is upcurved and anteriorly directed (
Fig. 46
); and the cuspis has dense posteriorly directed plumose setae (
Figs 44–46
).

Remarks. Metasomal shape, female mesosomal shape and male genitalia closely link Gogoltilla to some genera in the subtribe Pseudomethocina ( sensu Brothers 1975 , 1999 ). First, the parameres are dorsoventrally flattened and initially downcurved (
Fig. 46
); second, the penis valve is asetose (
Fig. 47
); third, the first tergite is subsessile with the second (
Fig. 40–43
); and finally, the female mesosoma is sharply constricted anterior to the propodeal spiracle in dorsal view (
Fig. 40
).
